"I did not realized this was 15% ABV until pouring. My god. Pours a translucent ruby/carmel color with the thinnest of heads that leaves but trace amounts of lacing on the sides of the glass. The nose is a mix of caramel and alcohol. You KNOW this is one boozy bastard. The taste affirms the smell, this is an alcohol bomb. There's some subtle hints of caramel, toffee, and vanilla, but the alcohol dominates through and through. This right here will take the chill off any December day, regardless of the line of latitude upon which you reside. The mouthfeel is hot as hell. Let a mouthful of this rest on your palate for 10-15 seconds, and it feels like the insides of your mouth are being dissolved. It's very astringent and has a monster bite.The aftertaste is just...boozy. Someone could smell this on your breath from several meters out. Don't drink this and expect a pleasant response from the po-po if you can pulled over on the way home. Overall, this is a pass. Not a big fan. I'd recommend sharing even a 12 oz. bottle among 3-4 people. I will say, I'd be curious as to what this could turn into after being layed down for 5 years. But, it needs time. It needs something. It's current state just does nothing for me in a landscape full of luscious barleywines."
