"Beautiful Copper body topped by a thick tan head, really thick for a 15% ABV beer. Head retention is also very good. Aroma is incredibly sweet malt with brown sugar and fruit notes. Aroma is so good I could just hold it to my nose and be pretty happy. Slight alcoholic note, but this is after my 7th or 8th deep inhale. Give me a few more minutes of sniffing...OK I'm back. Flavor - surprisingly light after such a powerful scent. It's incredible that this body and flavor come from this beer. Actually well balanced, decent bitterness to support the malt; finishes with a lingering metallic note and a touch of rubbing alcohol, but it's not really detracting from the flavor. But this is the antithesis of the overly sweet big barleywine. It reminds me of a beer with a touch of vodka - still powerful, but not heavy bodied. Mouthfeel is good; very impressive lighter body for such a big beer. Drinkability is actually very good. This drinks more like a strong amber ale than one of the stronger barleywines available. Been a while since I had a DFH beer; forgot how well crafted they can be."
